 the parent organization anthem and wellpoint achieved a portion of this growth through mergers and acquisitions wellpoint inc was formed in november  following a merger of anthem and wellpoint health networks inc the merger was structured as anthem acquiring wellpoint health networks and rebranding itself wellpoint inc when the deal was originally announced in october  the merger was set at  billion the fair market value of the merger when completed in december  was approximately  billion at the time of the mergers completion wellpoint was the largest american insurer in december  wellpoint changed its corporate name to anthem inc timelineedit anthemassociated insuranceedit s anthem began in indianapolis indiana as mutual hospital insurance inc and mutual medical insurance inc the companies grew significantly controlling  of the medical insurance market in indiana by the s  the two firms now known as blue cross of indiana and blue shield of indiana entered into a joint operating agreement s anthem inc began as an insurance company as a spinoff of the group insurance operations of american general insurance  the two merged into associated insurance companies inc a holding company but usage of the name anthem persisted  associated insurance companies began expanding outside of indiana acquiring numerous insurance companies and creating new subsidiaries  associated insurance companies changed its name to the associated group to coincide with its expanded focus associated insurances acquisitions included anthem health inc a national company offering group life and health insurance raffensperger hughes  co inc indianas largest investment bank and the shelby insurance co a property and casualty insurance business the associated groupedit  the associated group founded acordia brokerage that sold and serviced insurance and employee benefit programs  the associated group took acordia  acordia acquired american business insurance for  million and the federal kemper insurance