m insurance companyedit anthem insurance company grew out of two indianapolis indiana based mutual insurance companies mutual hospital insurance inc and mutual medical insurance inc formed in  and  the companies grew significantly controlling  of the medical insurance market in indiana by the s in  they came together to create a joint operating agreement and merged in  as parent company associated insurance companies inc to form blue cross and blue shield of indiana in  associated insurance companies changed its name to the associated group tag to reflect its expanded focus and began heavily expanding outside indiana acquiring numerous insurance companies and creating new subsidiaries throughout the late s through the mids formerly anthem inc was an insurance company which began in the s as a spinoff of the group insurance operations of american general insurance anthem blue cross and blue shield was created as part of the merger of the associated group with community mutual insurance co of cincinnati from its move to a publicly traded company in  until its final merger in  it merged the blue cross blue shield organizations of several states to achieve economy of scale converting them in the process from nonprofit to forprofit status in late  anthem and wellpoint merged with the combined company taking the wellpoint name that anthem no longer exists as a company but the anthem blue cross and blue shield brand name is used by wellpoint in  states in october  anthem demutualized and conducted an initial public offering of common stock wellpoint inc formerly anthem inc was formed when wellpoint health networks inc and anthem inc merged in  to become the nations leading health benefits company wellpoint health network incs predecessor was blue cross of california which was founded in  with the consolidation of blue cross of northern california established in  and blue cross of southern california established in  wellpoint was formed in  to operate blue cross of californias managed care business in  blue cross of california spun off its managed care business into a separate publicly traded entity wellpoint health networks inc in  blue cross of california completed the conversion of all its business to forprofit status resulting in a restructuring that designated wellpoint health networks inc as the parent organization anthem and wellpoint achieved a portion of this growth through mergers and acquisitions wellpoint inc was formed in november  following a merger of anthem and wellpoint health networks inc the merger was structured as anthem acquiring wellpoint health networks and rebranding itself wellpoint inc when the deal was originally announced in october  the merger was set at  billion the fair market value of the merger when completed in december  was approximately  billion at the time of the mergers completion wellpoint was the largest american insurer in december  wellpoint changed its corporate name to anthem inc timelineedit anthemassociated insuranceedit s anthem began in indianapolis indiana as mutual hospital insurance inc and mutual medical insurance inc the companies grew significantly controlling  of the medical insurance market in indiana by the s  the two firms now known as blue cross of indiana and blue shield of indiana entered into a joint operating agreement s anthem inc began as an insurance company as a spinoff of the group insurance operations of american general insurance  the two merged into associated insurance companies inc a holding company but usage of the name anthem persisted  associated insurance companies began expanding outside of indiana acquiring numerous insurance companies and creating new subsidiaries  associated insurance companies changed its name to the associated group to coincide with its expanded focus associated insurances acquisitions included anthem health inc a national company offering group life and health insurance raffensperger hughes  co inc indianas largest investment bank and